FBIS4-57413 "drlat097_a_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-097 Daily Report 17 May 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Water Company Announces Shortages in Havana City Water Company Announces Shortages in Havana City FL1805000494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 17 May 94 FL1805000494 Havana Radio Reloj Network Spanish BFN [Text] The Havana City water company has informed the people that because of problems in the water pumping system in the Cuatro Caminos supply station, there will be a water shortage tomorrow, 18 June, in several municipalities in Havana City. Water supply will be suspended from 0600 to 1800 in the zones of Cotorro, Guanabacoa, and La Habana del Este. The municipality of Cotorro, the town of Cuatro Caminos, and its outskirts will be affected. In Guanabacoa, the water shortage will affect the areas around Monumental Avenue, from the Central Highway to the towns of Santa Fe and Bacuranao; and in the municipality of La Habana del Este, the localities of Guiteras, Cojimar, and the Alamar development zone. The Havana water company apologizes for the problems this shortage might cause. It adds that once the repair work is finished, the water service will be gradually reestablished.
